      "message": "This feels weird, because `null` can also mean a legitimate error occurred. AFAICS the only time this special case comes up at all is `sk_FragColor`. Unfortunately from here, there\u0027s no good way AFAICS to distinguish the error case from the `sk_FragColor` case without hard-coding in some extra special-case magic, and it feels wrong to let the special-case treatment \"leak\" outside of the IRGenerator.\n\nHere\u0027s an alternative idea: what if we had a dedicated accessor function `sk_FragColor()` (kind of like `sk_SampleCoord()`)? It can just assume that `sk_FragColor` exists in the symbol table and yoink it out. Then DeclareGlobal doesn\u0027t need to think about sk_FragColor.",
